<p><ent>Scrawl</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Scrawl
<hw>Scrawl</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Scrawled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Scrawling</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Probably corrupted from
<ets>scrabble</ets>.]</ety> <def>To draw or mark awkwardly and
irregularly; to write hastily and carelessly; to scratch; to scribble;
<as>as, to <ex>scrawl</ex> a letter</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His name, <qex>scrawled</qex> by himself.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scrawl</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Scrawl
<hw>Scrawl</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To write unskillfully and
inelegantly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Though with a golden pen you <qex>scrawl</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Swift.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1292 pr=PCP --></p>

<p><ent>Scrawl</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Scrawl
<hw>Scrawl</hw> <pr>(skr⟦add⟧l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Unskillful or
inelegant writing; that which is unskillfully or inelegantly
written.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The left hand will make such a <qex>scrawl</qex>, that it will not
be legible.</q> <rj><qau>Arbuthnot.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>You bid me write no more than a <qex>scrawl</qex> to you.</q>
<rj><qau>Gray.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scrawler</ent>⟦br⟧
